# Architecture

## Module Layout

```
src/
├── engine/          # Core loop, registry, entity primitives
├── math/            # vec3, quat, mat4 — no deps, no classes
├── input/           # createInput — keyboard, mouse, pointer lock
├── collision/       # Pure AABB/OBB math helpers (no GL, no registry)
├── components/      # Shared data-only component types + factories
│   ├── transform    # position, yaw, scale, world matrix
│   ├── renderable   # mesh + material + optional model matrix
│   ├── collider     # AABB / ObbY — static or dynamic
│   ├── skin         # skinning palette for skeletal meshes
│   └── animation    # clip sampling, retargeting
├── assets/gltf/     # GLB/glTF loader, runtime scene, materials builder
├── render/          # WebGL2 device, passes, pipeline installer
│   ├── gl/          # device, mesh, shader, texture, framebuffers
│   ├── passes/      # ShadowPass, ForwardPass, PostProcessPass, AsciiPostProcessPass
│   ├── shaders/     # GLSL source split by concern (shadow, lit, ground, post, ascii)
│   └── pipeline.ts  # installRenderPipeline → RenderPipeline
├── systems/         # Registry system installers (character, camera, animation, …)
├── player/          # Player entity assembly + player-specific components
│   ├── components/  # characterController, cameraFollow
│   └── player.ts    # createPlayer — entity assembly + asset loading
├── world/           # World geometry helpers
│   ├── ground.ts    # createGroundMesh
│   └── staticProps.ts # instantiateStaticProp
└── startup/
    └── bootstrap.ts # Composition root — wire systems, load assets, game.start()
```

## Naming Conventions

| Pattern | Example | Use for |
|---------|---------|---------|
| `createX()` | `createTransform()` | Data factory — returns a plain object |
| `installXSystem()` | `installCharacterSystem()` | System installer — registers actions on registry |
| `useX()` | `useRegistry()` | Engine primitive — creates and owns internal state |
| `buildX()` | `buildGltfMaterials()` | Pure transform/builder — no side effects |

## Code Style

- Arrow functions everywhere; `function` keyword only in module-level helpers inside `.ts` files
- No `class` in game logic; `class` is acceptable only in render passes where constructor injection is cleaner
- Factory functions return plain typed objects — never extend or subclass them
- Every public-facing factory/installer exports its return type explicitly
- Guard throws at entry: `if (!canvas) throw new Error('Missing #game canvas')`
- **Never** add barrel `index.ts` files — import directly from the concrete module (e.g. `../engine/registry.ts`, not `../engine` or `../engine/index.ts`)

## Adding New Features

Follow the manaburn-barcrawl pattern — add a feature folder:
```
src/enemies/spider/
  spider.ts           # createSpiderEntity
  components/
    spiderAI.ts
  systems/
    spiderSystem.ts   # installSpiderSystem
```
Register in `bootstrap.ts` with a call to `installSpiderSystem(registry, staticColliders)`.
